The paper deals with the processing of instruction streams in a remote execution environment, which suggests that it may fall under the Distributed Systems category (cs.DC) or the Programming Languages category (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the behaviour of instruction sequences and the control of that behaviour, which could also place it in the Software Engineering category (cs.SE). Finally, the mention of a protocol for instruction stream processing suggests that the paper may also fall under the Architecture category (cs.AR).
